{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:17:51.888Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Perceptron"},{"type":"text","text":" is the simplest form of an artificial neural network—a single neuron that makes decisions by combining inputs with weights, adding a bias, and applying an activation function. It's the foundational building block of all neural networks, including Multilayer Perceptrons (MLPs) used in Generative AI."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What the Perceptron Is"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A single artificial neuron that performs binary classification"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Origin"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduced by Frank Rosenblatt in 1957 at Cornell Aeronautical Laboratory, inspired by biological neurons"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Purpose"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supervised learning for binary classification tasks (output: 0 or 1)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Capability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can only classify "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"linearly separable data"},{"type":"text","text":" (data separable by a straight line/plane)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works (The Math)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The perceptron computes its output through these steps:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Input values"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"x_1, x_2, \\dots, x_n"}},{"type":"text","text":" (numerical features)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Weights"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"w_1, w_2, \\dots, w_n"}},{"type":"text","text":" (learned during training)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Bias"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"b"}},{"type":"text","text":" (threshold that shifts the decision boundary)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Weighted sum"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"z = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} w_i x_i + b = \\mathbf{w} \\cdot \\mathbf{x} + b"}}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Activation function"},{"type":"text","text":": Applies a step function (original) or sigmoid/logistic function:"}]}]}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\text{output} = g(z) = \\begin{cases} \n   1 & \\text{if } z \\geq 0 \\\\\n   0 & \\text{if } z < 0\n   \\end{cases}"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[quantstart](https://www.quantstart.com/articles/introduction-to-artificial-neural-networks-and-the-perceptron/)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visually, the perceptron creates a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"decision boundary"},{"type":"text","text":" (a line in 2D, plane in 3D) that separates two classes of data."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why the Perceptron Matters (and Its Limitation)"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Important"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Limitation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fundamental building block of neural networks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Only handles "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"linearly separable"},{"type":"text","text":" problems"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduces core concepts: weights, bias, activation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cannot solve non-linear problems like XOR or complex patterns"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Historical foundation for deep learning"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single perceptron = too simple for real-world tasks"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"From Perceptron to Multilayer Perceptron (MLP)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MLP"},{"type":"text","text":" solves the perceptron's limitation by stacking multiple perceptrons into layers:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Feature"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single Perceptron"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multilayer Perceptron (MLP)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structure"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"One neuron"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Input layer + "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hidden layers"},{"type":"text","text":" + output layer"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Connectivity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"N/A"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fully connected: every neuron connects to all neurons in next layer"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Activation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step function (original)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-linear"},{"type":"text","text":" functions (ReLU, sigmoid, tanh)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Capability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Linear classification only"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Learns "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"complex non-linear patterns"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple weight update"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backpropagation"},{"type":"text","text":" to minimize error"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": The non-linear activation functions in hidden layers allow MLPs to learn patterns that single perceptrons cannot, making them foundational for modern deep learning and Generative AI."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of the perceptron as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single decision-maker"},{"type":"text","text":" asking: \"Is the weighted input above this threshold?\" An MLP is like a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"team of decision-makers"},{"type":"text","text":" in layers, where each layer builds on the previous one's decisions to solve complex problems."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The perceptron is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"simplest neural network unit"},{"type":"text","text":"—a single binary classifier"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It computes: "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\text{output} = g(\\mathbf{w} \\cdot \\mathbf{x} + b)"}}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Limitation"},{"type":"text","text":": Only solves linearly separable problems"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"MLP"},{"type":"text","text":" stacks multiple perceptrons with non-linear activations to learn complex patterns"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MLPs are trained via "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"backpropagation"},{"type":"text","text":" and are fundamental to deep learning"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is why understanding the perceptron is essential before diving into MLPs and modern neural networks in Generative AI."}]}]}}
